directions: ["In 10-inch skillet, brown beef cubes in hot oil.", "Stir in wine, undrained tomatoes, onion, green pepper, raisins, apricots, salt, pepper and garlic.", "In a cheesecloth bag, combine basil, thyme, tarragon and bay leaf.", "Add to meat mixture and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.", "Stir mushrooms and olives into stew. Simmer, covered, 30 minutes more.", "Discard herb bag.", "Blend cold water with flour; stir into stew.", "Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.", "Serve over rice.", "Makes 6 servings."]
NER: ["tomatoes", "cold water", "tarragon", "beef stew meat", "mushrooms", "onion", "raisins", "basil", "thyme", "flour", "olives", "green pepper", "salt", "pepper", "cooking oil", "clove garlic", "red wine", "dried apricots", "bay leaf"]

title: Cinnamon Nuts
ingredients: ["1 c. sugar", "1 tsp. cinnamon", "1/3 c. canned cream", "1 tsp. vanilla", "1 1/2 c. nuts"]
directions: ["Mix cinnamon into sugar; add cream and mix well.", "Cook on medium-low heat, stirring constantly; cook to 240\u00b0.", "Remove from heat.", "Add vanilla and nuts.", "Stir until syrup coats nuts.", "Spread on wax paper to cool.", "Break into pieces."]

title: Pineapple Cheese Ball
ingredients: ["2 pkg. (8 oz. size) cream cheese, softened", "1 c. crushed pineapple, drained", "2 c. chopped pecans", "1/4 c. finely chopped green pepper", "1 tsp. seasoned salt", "maraschino cherries (optional)", "parsley sprigs (optional)", "2 Tbsp. finely chopped onion", "assorted crackers"]
directions: ["In medium bowl with fork, beat cream cheese until smooth. Gradually stir in crushed pineapple, 1 cup pecans, green pepper, onion and salt.", "Shape into a ball. Roll in remaining nuts.", "Wrap in plastic film or foil.", "Refrigerate until well chilled, overnight."]

title: Fruit Cobbler
ingredients: ["6 c. fruit", "4 Tbsp. tapioca", "1 1/2 c. sugar", "2 c. flour", "3 tsp. baking powder", "1 tsp. salt", "2/3 c. oil", "2 eggs", "1/2 c. milk"]
directions: ["Mix fruit, tapioca and sugar.", "Pour in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.", "Mix other ingredients and drop by spoonfuls on top of fruit. Bake 40 minutes at 350\u00b0."]
